Here. Oh, boy.

232
00:13:52,970 --> 00:13:54,999
Here. My goodness.

233
00:13:55,000 --> 00:13:57,740
Women shouldn't be walking around
alone at this late hour.

234
00:13:57,740 --> 00:13:59,940
Let's go. I'll walk you home.

235
00:13:59,940 --> 00:14:01,879
It's fine. I got this.

236
00:14:01,879 --> 00:14:03,539
No, it's not fine!

237
00:14:03,539 --> 00:14:06,008
I can tell that you have bad knees.

238
00:14:06,009 --> 00:14:08,548
Let's go. Lead the way.

239
00:14:08,549 --> 00:14:10,529
I'll push the cart from behind.

240
00:14:11,919 --> 00:14:13,929
Okay, let's go!

241
00:14:14,519 --> 00:14:17,039
I'll be back in a minute.
Wait right there!

242
00:14:17,590 --> 00:14:18,970
What the...

243
00:14:30,070 --> 00:14:33,990
I can't give her name to save my skin.

244
00:14:34,980 --> 00:14:36,210
Detective Geum...

245
00:14:36,210 --> 00:14:37,580
(Model Detective Award Ceremony)

246
00:14:37,580 --> 00:14:40,808
He was the first man...

247
00:14:40,809 --> 00:14:43,579
to treat me like a person,
like a human being.

248
00:14:43,580 --> 00:14:46,470
(A Detective's Good Deed)

249
00:14:46,789 --> 00:14:48,169
What...

250
00:14:49,120 --> 00:14:50,500
"Good deed?"

251
00:14:53,029 --> 00:14:56,009
How is his brain wired?

252
00:15:23,190 --> 00:15:24,669
Do you want to join me?

253
00:15:33,500 --> 00:15:34,880
Cherri.

254
00:15:34,929 --> 00:15:38,179
A daily getaway. Do you want to join me?

255
00:15:38,509 --> 00:15:40,320
She looks so human.

256
00:15:47,549 --> 00:15:55,870
(A daily getaway. Do you want to join me?)

257
00:16:17,679 --> 00:16:19,259
Cherri, turn on the TV.

258
00:16:20,149 --> 00:16:21,759
Turning on the TV.

259
00:16:22,080 --> 00:16:25,549
This movie that you will like
is now available.

260
00:16:25,549 --> 00:16:27,449
Would you like to watch it with me?

261
00:16:27,450 --> 00:16:28,840
Sure.

262
00:16:29,820 --> 00:16:31,860
Yes, that's right.

263
00:16:31,860 --> 00:16:33,460
I can't believe this.

264
00:16:33,460 --> 00:16:36,898
You need to tell me these things!

265
00:16:36,899 --> 00:16:38,679
I'm home.

266
00:16:40,230 --> 00:16:43,000
Then tomorrow morning...

267
00:16:43,000 --> 00:16:45,019
Who...

268
00:16:45,210 --> 00:16:46,689
Who are you?

269
00:16:46,970 --> 00:16:48,038
What?

270
00:16:48,039 --> 00:16:49,439
Who are you?

271
00:16:49,440 --> 00:16:52,090
What do you mean? I'm your wife.

272
00:16:52,509 --> 00:16:54,860
Do you not recognize me
because I got home too early today?

273
00:17:05,960 --> 00:17:07,340
Cherri.

274
00:17:08,029 --> 00:17:09,409
What are you doing here?

275
00:17:09,559 --> 00:17:11,139
What's with you?

276
00:17:12,099 --> 00:17:13,749
Honey, are you drunk?

277
00:17:15,299 --> 00:17:16,679
How dare you set foot in here?

278
00:17:17,869 --> 00:17:19,249
Get out.

279
00:17:20,369 --> 00:17:22,120
Get out!

280
00:17:22,779 --> 00:17:24,579
- Get out!
- What's the matter with you?

281
00:17:24,579 --> 00:17:26,179
- What?
- What are you doing here?

282
00:17:26,180 --> 00:17:27,849
Get out. Go.

283
00:17:27,849 --> 00:17:29,800
- Honey, why...
- I said, get out!

284
00:17:30,880 --> 00:17:33,429
Hey, what are you doing? Open the door.

285
00:17:33,519 --> 00:17:34,899
Gosh.

286
00:17:39,730 --> 00:17:41,439
What are you doing?

287
00:17:41,559 --> 00:17:42,939
Open up at once.

288
00:17:43,059 --> 00:17:44,510
Have you lost your mind?

289
00:17:44,960 --> 00:17:46,350
Open the door!

290
00:18:01,609 --> 00:18:02,999
What are you doing here so early?

291
00:18:03,019 --> 00:18:04,319
Good morning!

292
00:18:04,319 --> 00:18:06,920
What do you think? I stopped by
to make breakfast for you.

293
00:18:06,920 --> 00:18:08,370
Eat up.

294
00:18:09,759 --> 00:18:12,669
- Cherri.
- Yes, what can I do for you?

295
00:18:13,029 --> 00:18:16,810
Cherri, play a song by N.Flying.

296
00:18:16,859 --> 00:18:19,209
Playing a song by N.Flying.

297
00:18:24,900 --> 00:18:26,350
You can do stuff like this?

298
00:18:26,609 --> 00:18:28,910
My, what an amazing world
we're living in these days.

299
00:18:28,910 --> 00:18:31,820
I can sing karaoke
and watch movies with her too.

300
00:18:31,950 --> 00:18:33,330
You can do all sorts of things.

301
00:18:33,910 --> 00:18:35,429
Come on. Don't be such a boomer.

302
00:18:36,849 --> 00:18:38,530
I am a boomer.

303
00:18:39,250 --> 00:18:41,630
This boomer has a question for you.

304
00:18:44,589 --> 00:18:46,588
What time did your dad
get home last night?

305
00:18:46,589 --> 00:18:47,689
No idea.

306
00:18:47,690 --> 00:18:50,810
I went to bed at 2 a.m.
He wasn't home until then.

307
00:18:51,230 --> 00:18:54,679
He didn't come home until 2 a.m.?
That fool...

308
00:18:55,599 --> 00:18:56,940
- But...
- Yes.

309
00:18:56,940 --> 00:18:58,679
he looked like he got into a fight.

310
00:18:58,769 --> 00:18:59,808
What?

311
00:18:59,809 --> 00:19:01,339
I checked his clothes.

312
00:19:01,339 --> 00:19:03,939
They were all stretched out and soiled.

313
00:19:03,940 --> 00:19:05,320
No joke.

314
00:19:05,450 --> 00:19:06,830
Really?

315
00:19:09,049 --> 00:19:11,199
Then he wasn't with a woman.

316
00:19:13,220 --> 00:19:16,999
Good morning! I prepared
a delicious breakfast for you.

317
00:19:18,759 --> 00:19:21,159
Don't you think this is too much?

318
00:19:21,160 --> 00:19:22,328
Well...

319
00:19:22,329 --> 00:19:25,479
I'm trying to be nice to my best friend.

320
00:19:27,670 --> 00:19:30,249
Even the ghost of a best friend
would find this extreme.

321
00:19:31,640 --> 00:19:33,039
Daughter, have a good day in school.

322
00:19:33,039 --> 00:19:35,068
- Sure.
- Where are you going?

323
00:19:35,069 --> 00:19:37,219
To work, of course!

324
00:19:38,240 --> 00:19:41,189
You should at least have a bite.

325
00:19:41,509 --> 00:19:43,530
(Gwangju Police Station,
Civil Service Center)

326
00:19:44,250 --> 00:19:47,100
(Civil Service Center)

327
00:19:56,529 --> 00:19:58,010
Excuse me.

328
00:19:59,329 --> 00:20:00,880
What is this about?

329
00:20:01,170 --> 00:20:03,179
Can I help you with something?

330
00:20:03,839 --> 00:20:05,989
Well, you see...

331
00:20:06,269 --> 00:20:07,749
My wife...

332
00:20:08,210 --> 00:20:10,020
has gone missing.

333
00:20:11,039 --> 00:20:13,290
- Missing?
- Yes.

334
00:20:13,450 --> 00:20:15,159
It has already been a week.

335
00:20:16,319 --> 00:20:18,659
I looked everywhere she could be,

336
00:20:19,549 --> 00:20:20,749
but I couldn't find her.

337
00:20:20,750 --> 00:20:23,219
Gosh, you must be deeply concerned.

338
00:20:23,220 --> 00:20:25,629
You need to file a police report first...

339
00:20:25,630 --> 00:20:27,490
with the Missing Persons Unit.

340
00:20:27,490 --> 00:20:29,909
Let me escort you. Come on.

341
00:20:31,029 --> 00:20:32,930
This is how it is
with adults who go missing.

342
00:20:32,930 --> 00:20:34,400
It starts with looking into...

343
00:20:34,400 --> 00:20:35,768
the possibility of them running away.

344
00:20:35,769 --> 00:20:38,768
The investigation
might seem slow at first,

345
00:20:38,769 --> 00:20:42,459
so the families could be frustrated.

346
00:20:42,779 --> 00:20:44,608
My wife has gone missing.

347
00:20:44,609 --> 00:20:46,479
Is there a reason to believe that?

348
00:20:46,480 --> 00:20:48,459
Did you notice anything weird?

349
00:20:50,619 --> 00:20:55,389
(Honorable Seobu Police Station)

350
00:20:55,390 --> 00:20:57,419
Someone must've hurt my wife.

351
00:20:57,420 --> 00:20:59,110
What makes you think that?

352
00:21:04,200 --> 00:21:05,639
Because I know.

353
00:21:05,769 --> 00:21:07,979
I know who hurt my wife.

354
00:21:10,400 --> 00:21:11,850
Who may that be?

355
00:21:15,579 --> 00:21:18,139
- It's Cherri.
- Who's Cherri?

356
00:21:18,140 --> 00:21:20,229
The virtual human.

357
00:21:21,180 --> 00:21:22,760
Cherri, the virtual human.

358
00:21:23,920 --> 00:21:25,330
You know her, right?

359
00:21:27,319 --> 00:21:30,159
The virtual human as in...

360
00:21:30,160 --> 00:21:32,859
"Turning TV on. Turning TV off."

361
00:21:32,859 --> 00:21:34,829
- The one who says that?
- Yes.

362
00:21:34,829 --> 00:21:37,098
The virtual human
that is in TV commercials...

363
00:21:37,099 --> 00:21:39,768
and on beer labels. That Cherri?

364
00:21:39,769 --> 00:21:43,120
That's right.
I think she got rid of my wife.

365
00:21:49,079 --> 00:21:50,508
Could you tell me your name?

366
00:21:50,509 --> 00:21:53,530
Right. I'm Heo Bum Soo.

367
00:21:54,009 --> 00:21:55,489
Mr. Heo Bum Soo?

368
00:22:00,789 --> 00:22:03,058
- Where do you live?
- Will you come with me?

369
00:22:03,059 --> 00:22:05,139
She's at my house at the moment.

370
00:22:05,759 --> 00:22:07,429
- As in Cherri?
- Yes.

371
00:22:07,430 --> 00:22:08,430
She's at my place as well.

372
00:22:08,430 --> 00:22:11,999
She's alive outside the screen
and is walking around my house.

373
00:22:12,000 --> 00:22:13,449
Cherri, I mean.

374
00:22:14,569 --> 00:22:17,038
Are you saying that Cherri...

375
00:22:17,039 --> 00:22:19,940
took a human form and harmed your wife?

376
00:22:19,940 --> 00:22:21,409
That's right.

377
00:22:21,410 --> 00:22:22,939
Why...

378
00:22:22,940 --> 00:22:26,060
did Cherri do something so risky?

379
00:22:27,779 --> 00:22:29,699
Because she loves me.

380
00:22:43,822 --> 00:22:47,291
Hey. Captain Seul,
did you get home safely last night?

381
00:22:47,292 --> 00:22:48,672
I did.

382
00:22:49,392 --> 00:22:52,103
I just ran into a strange man just now.

383
00:22:55,332 --> 00:22:56,561
It's fine.

384
00:22:56,562 --> 00:22:59,813
He came by to report his wife missing.

385
00:22:59,973 --> 00:23:02,732
Apparently, someone hurt his wife.

386
00:23:02,733 --> 00:23:05,601
He's claiming that it was Cherri.

387
00:23:05,602 --> 00:23:07,512
You know that AI program, right?

388
00:23:07,513 --> 00:23:11,162
The one that helps you
turn the TV on and off.

389
00:23:11,443 --> 00:23:13,192
The name rings a bell.

390
00:23:15,013 --> 00:23:16,533
Captain?

391
00:23:17,183 --> 00:23:18,752
You should consult Dr. Brain.

392
00:23:18,753 --> 00:23:20,172
Captain?

393
00:23:21,693 --> 00:23:25,073
She must still be hungover
from all that she drank last night.

394
00:23:25,562 --> 00:23:27,613
She'll be hurling for sure.

395
00:23:28,763 --> 00:23:31,482
Darn it. Dr. Brain, did she say?

396
00:23:36,302 --> 00:23:37,682
Darn you!

397
00:23:38,542 --> 00:23:41,442
Let's fight man to man
and put an end to this, you jerk.

398
00:23:41,443 --> 00:23:43,623
We're in agreement for once.

399
00:23:47,812 --> 00:23:50,403
I doubt he'll be civil about this.

400
00:23:51,523 --> 00:23:53,621
Were you desperate
for an earful this morning?

401
00:23:53,622 --> 00:23:55,172
Why are you calling?

402
00:23:55,592 --> 00:23:58,373
I don't want to talk to you, so...

403
00:24:00,392 --> 00:24:03,783
A virtual human hurt his wife?

404
00:24:04,203 --> 00:24:05,912
And his wife is missing?

405
00:24:07,572 --> 00:24:10,641
Where did he say this virtual human was?

406
00:24:10,642 --> 00:24:11,903
At home.

407
00:24:11,903 --> 00:24:14,123
He said that it was in human form.

408
00:24:15,173 --> 00:24:18,781
Then go to his house
and meet Cherri in person.

409
00:24:18,782 --> 00:24:20,692
That will answer a lot of your questions.

410
00:24:20,882 --> 00:24:23,483
Don't forget to call me when you meet her.

411
00:24:23,483 --> 00:24:24,722
Aren't you coming with?

412
00:24:24,723 --> 00:24:26,363
Why should I accompany you?

413
00:24:27,423 --> 00:24:29,862
You always accompany me
when I'm out in the field,

414
00:24:29,862 --> 00:24:31,903
but now you're staying back.

415
00:24:32,062 --> 00:24:34,412
Why is that? Are you upset about
what happened yesterday?

416
00:24:34,463 --> 00:24:36,831
Let's not be petty about this.

417
00:24:36,832 --> 00:24:39,783
Men sometimes
get into physical altercations...

418
00:24:41,332 --> 00:24:43,853
Hello? Dr. Brain?

419
00:24:45,003 --> 00:24:46,853
He's moping for sure.

420
00:24:53,913 --> 00:24:55,393
Was it that detective?

421
00:24:57,483 --> 00:24:58,782
Yes, I think we have...

422
00:24:58,782 --> 00:25:01,133
another interesting case on our hands.

423
00:25:01,622 --> 00:25:04,091
It's that detective who interests me more.

424
00:25:04,092 --> 00:25:06,403
The man hasn't done
a bad deed in his life.

425
00:25:06,693 --> 00:25:08,573
But I haven't been digging that much.

426
00:25:08,862 --> 00:25:10,783
I'm going to dig deeper.

427
00:25:11,532 --> 00:25:13,301
That's enough.

428
00:25:13,302 --> 00:25:16,571
I agree that he inconvenienced you,

429
00:25:16,572 --> 00:25:19,583
but I don't think
he's as bad as you think.

430
00:25:20,642 --> 00:25:22,842
A middle-aged brain like mine...

431
00:25:22,842 --> 00:25:24,563
develops gut feelings.

432
00:25:25,612 --> 00:25:27,593
I don't see him as someone bad.

433
00:25:29,282 --> 00:25:32,962
What he's actually like
is for me to find out.

434
00:25:33,792 --> 00:25:35,603
I'm going to study...

435
00:25:36,153 --> 00:25:37,942
how is brain is structured.

436
00:25:44,562 --> 00:25:45,942
Right.

437
00:25:45,963 --> 00:25:48,912
Cherri is now in human form?

438
00:25:49,903 --> 00:25:52,383
She'd better be here or else.

439
00:25:52,903 --> 00:25:54,823
Unit 603.

440
00:25:56,042 --> 00:25:58,563
(Press unit number.)

441
00:26:01,782 --> 00:26:03,081
Who is it?

442
00:26:03,082 --> 00:26:05,133
Is this Mr. Heo Bum Soo?

443
00:26:05,223 --> 00:26:07,122
I'm Detective Geum Myung Se...

444
00:26:07,122 --> 00:26:09,502
whom you met
at the police station earlier...

445
00:26:10,822 --> 00:26:12,543
(Call disconnected)

446
00:26:13,023 --> 00:26:14,543
What the...

447
00:26:30,713 --> 00:26:32,393
(Press unit number.)

448
00:26:43,253 --> 00:26:45,873
But I know he's home.

449
00:26:47,292 --> 00:26:49,891
Dr. Brain was right.

450
00:26:49,892 --> 00:26:51,482
Something's up.

451
00:27:04,642 --> 00:27:07,232
Sir. Excuse me.

452
00:27:08,582 --> 00:27:09,752
Yes?

453
00:27:09,753 --> 00:27:11,333
I'm Detective Geum Myung Se...

454
00:27:12,023 --> 00:27:13,972
from the Seobu Police Station.

455
00:27:13,993 --> 00:27:15,672
The wife must've reported him.

456
00:27:16,153 --> 00:27:18,772
- Sorry?
- For domestic violence.

457
00:27:19,862 --> 00:27:22,272
No, I'm here for something else.

458
00:27:23,132 --> 00:27:24,643
Did something happen?

459
00:27:25,362 --> 00:27:28,752
Well, a while ago,

460
00:27:29,032 --> 00:27:31,123
I found her outside devastated.

461
00:27:37,683 --> 00:27:40,323
He had kicked her out of the house.

462
00:27:41,112 --> 00:27:43,093
He kept on getting her to leave.

463
00:27:44,282 --> 00:27:45,582
This one time,

464
00:27:45,582 --> 00:27:47,291
I heard someone screaming
and the sounds of an argument.

465
00:27:47,292 --> 00:27:48,803
It was a mess.

466
00:27:51,792 --> 00:27:54,073
This didn't come from me though.

467
00:28:03,173 --> 00:28:06,383
Detective, what brings you by?

468
00:28:16,052 --> 00:28:18,502
I'm here to see Cherri.

